# Slice S1 -- Land the ANN harness fix + EU-8 IR harness on main

## Model + effort
Launched as `claude -p --model claude-opus-4-7 --effort high` inside a git worktree.

## Context (why this slice exists -- read first)
The 0.7.2 "recall gap" was root-caused as a MEASUREMENT ARTIFACT, not an engine
defect (corrected ANN recall@10 = 0.937, clears the 0.90 floor). The two harness
commits below ARE the real deliverable of that investigation and were ruled LAND
regardless of the PR-2b/2c keep/shelve outcome. This slice lands them on main and
adds one observability fix.

Required reading (do not re-derive):
- `dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2bc-decision.md` (RATIFIED decision memo; this slice = "LAND").
- `dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2c-recall-rootcause.md` -- esp. the TL;DR and the
  "Follow-up TODO: log the silent ground-truth-embed phase" section at the very
  end (that TODO is task 3 below).
- `dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-EU-8-ir-recall-results.md` (what the EU-8 harness measures).

## Mandate
Bring two already-built, already-measured harness commits onto this worktree branch
(orchestrator will cherry-pick the branch to main on codex PASS), then add the
GT-embed progress logging the root-cause doc calls for. NO engine behavior change.

### Task 1 -- cherry-pick the ANN harness fix `a601d1c`
`git cherry-pick a601d1c`. It contains:
- `eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs`: `measure_recall` now computes BOTH OLD (exclude-after +
  set-GT) AND NEW (exclude-before + dedup-GT) recall, isolating the +7.8pp
  measurement artifact; NEW=0.937 clears 0.90.
- `lib.rs`: an env-gated `EU7_SEARCH_LIMIT` seam in `read_search_in_tx` that
  defaults to `LIMIT 10` -- a PRODUCTION NO-OP (the env var is only ever set by the
  recall harness). Confirm this on inspection; it must not change production search.
- `candle_dump.rs` (new test): candle==HF embedding agreement check.
This was verified by the orchestrator to cherry-pick onto main with zero conflicts.

### Task 2 -- cherry-pick the EU-8 IR harness (`07f1a76` then `5658d39`)
`git cherry-pick 07f1a76 5658d39` (in that order). These add
`tests/eu8_ir_validation.rs` + a `tests/support/corpus_subset.rs` extension + the
EU-8 measurements JSON + the design note update. Engine `src/` is byte-unchanged by
both. Resolve any `corpus_subset.rs` conflict additively (keep both main's and the
EU-8 helper additions). If a conflict is non-trivial, STOP and report.

### Task 3 -- add `EU7_GT_EMBED_PROGRESS` periodic logging
In `eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs`, the harness re-embeds the entire corpus single-threaded
to build the in-Rust f32 ground truth, emitting NO output for ~25-45 min (this has
twice looked like a hang). Add, mirroring the existing `EU7_SEED_PROGRESS` throttled
`Instant` pattern:
1. a `GT_EMBED_START n=<n>` line immediately before the GT-embed loop, and
2. a throttled in-loop line (every ~30s or every K docs):
   `EU7_GT_EMBED_PROGRESS embedded=<i>/<n> rate_docs_per_s=<r>`.
Test-only; no behavior change. Find the loop by searching for the
`for body in &bodies[...]` / `doc_vecs.push(embedder.embed(...))` GT-build region.

