Refs: [0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-output.json](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-output.json:4), [0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-output.json](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-output.json:18)

The code fix resolves the prior BLOCK, but the closure artifact is not fully corrected. `head_sha` still points at pre-fix commit `f5bd686`, and `notes` still repeats the old overclaim that the `EU7_SEARCH_LIMIT` env seam was a verified production no-op at `lib.rs:3169`. Line 17 adds the correct fix-1 explanation, so the JSON is now internally inconsistent rather than fully repaired.

**What passed on inspection**

- The BLOCK itself is resolved. The vector rerank path no longer reads `EU7_SEARCH_LIMIT` or any other env var: `search_inner` loads `search_limit_override`, clamps it with `.max(SEARCH_RERANK_LIMIT)`, threads it through `ReaderRequest::Search`, and `read_search_in_tx` consumes only the passed `final_limit` ([lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1851), [lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1861), [lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3195)).
- Default production behavior remains the original `LIMIT 10`. The atomic initializes to `SEARCH_RERANK_LIMIT`, the effective value is floored at 10, and the SQL limit is still 10 when no override is set ([lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:561), [lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1854), [lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2943)).
- The new seam can only raise the effective limit. `set_search_limit_for_test` writes the atomic, but the search path clamps at `>= 10`; in-repo usage exists only in the EU-7 harness ([lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2445), [eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:444)).
- `measure_recall` switched from the env-based assumption to `set_search_limit_for_test(10 + RECALL_SEARCH_SLACK)` without changing the OLD/NEW recall logic in fix-1; GT-embed progress logging remains test-only in the harness file ([eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:431), [eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S1-20260531T125459Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:715)).
- EU-8 remained engine/embedder-source clean. Commits `519079c` and `75251fe` touch only docs/tests/JSON; across `2cd6e11..5b69568`, the only `src/.../src` file changed is engine `lib.rs`. `candle_dump` logging/env gating is test-only.

